race.comment: MR MILLER CREEK (6) is yet to break through after four starts and looks close to a win despite missing the placings last time over 402m at The Albuquerque Downs Racetrack & Casino (Dirt). Has a decent record at this trip with three minor placings from four tries and is among the leading chances. EL FENIX (9) was prominent in running on debut six-and-a-half months ago and battled on well for second over 274m at Sunland Park (Dirt). Has not been produced since. Likely improver and is among the main hopes. PER SUIT OF HAPPYNES (12) is a six-start maiden who could only manage to finish fifth at his latest appearance over 302m at this track (Dirt). Suited in this line up and is among the better hopes. FLYING DIAMOND MV (2) returned from a spell two-and-a-half weeks ago when he was beaten 4 lengths into ninth over 366m at this track. Strips fitter and can feature in the finish. Something for the Multiples: BAR FAVORITO (4)
